Petropavlovsk, Fresnillo Rise on Higher Gold, Silver Prices

-- B y   A m a n d a   J o r d a n
-- 
2011-07-14T16:15:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-14/petropavlovsk-fresnillo-rise-on-higher-gold-silver-prices-1-.html
Petropavlovsk Plc (POG)  and  Fresnillo Plc (FRES) ,
London-traded producers of precious metals, rose to a two-month
high in the city after gold and silver prices climbed.  Petropavlovsk advanced 3.3 percent to 823.5 pence, the
highest closing price since May 13, as of 4:30 p.m. local time.
Fresnillo increased 4.9 percent to 1,595 pence, the highest
price since May 3.  Gold futures for August delivery were little changed at
$1,585.60 an ounce on the Comex in New York, after earlier
rising as much as 0.6 percent to a record. Silver for September
delivery climbed as much as 3.3 percent to $39.395 an ounce.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Amanda Jordan in London at 
